To check if another ability is active that differs from the ability you want to activate in GAS, you can use the `GetActiveAbilitiesWithTags` function from the `UAbilitySystemComponent`. Here's an example:

1. First, create a function in your character or player controller class that takes the ability class or ability tags as input and returns a boolean indicating if another ability is active:

```cpp
UCLASS()
class YOURGAME_API AYourCharacter : public ACharacter
{
    GENERATED_BODY()

    // ...

public:
    UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category = "Abilities")
    bool IsAnotherAbilityActive(TSubclassOf<UGameplayAbility> AbilityToActivate, FGameplayTagContainer IgnoreAbilityTags);
};
```

2. Implement the function in your `.cpp` file:

```cpp
bool AYourCharacter::IsAnotherAbilityActive(TSubclassOf<UGameplayAbility> AbilityToActivate, FGameplayTagContainer IgnoreAbilityTags)
{
    UAbilitySystemComponent* AbilitySystemComponent = GetAbilitySystemComponent(); // You may have a different function to get the AbilitySystemComponent.
    if (AbilitySystemComponent)
    {
        TArray<FGameplayAbilitySpec*> ActiveAbilities;
        AbilitySystemComponent->GetActiveAbilitiesWithTags(IgnoreAbilityTags, ActiveAbilities);

        // Iterate through the active abilities
        for (FGameplayAbilitySpec* ActiveAbilitySpec : ActiveAbilities)
        {
            // Check if it's a different ability than the one we want to activate
            if (ActiveAbilitySpec->Ability->GetClass() != AbilityToActivate)
            {
                return true;
            }
        }
    }

    return false;
}
```

3. When you want to activate a new ability, call this function to check if another ability is active before attempting to activate the new one:

```cpp
TSubclassOf<UGameplayAbility> NewAbility = ...; // The ability you want to activate
FGameplayTagContainer IgnoreTags = ...; // The tags of the ability you want to ignore

if (!IsAnotherAbilityActive(NewAbility, IgnoreTags))
{
    GetAbilitySystemComponent()->TryActivateAbilityByClass(NewAbility);
}
```

This code will prevent the new ability from being activated if another ability with different tags is already active. Make sure to adjust the class names and function names according to your project. This should work in Unreal Engine 5.2 with the GAS plugin.

